				<td colspan="2" align="left"><div class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> some classes were unbalanced in single PvP (duel) and it was meant to be that way </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
That's a good thing, actually. In any game system that is balanced properly there will be no total equality between classes. Some classes will have a distinct advantage over one class, while another class has a distinct advantage over them. It's just the way things are, and if you try to make it all vanilla with everything dead equal you end up ruining the uniqueness of each class and dumbing down strategy and encounters.
<br />

<br />
If you are a Thief, you do NOT get into a hand to hand combat encounter with a Warrior, or you lose. Every time. You can, on the other hand, drop a Wizard in one shot by sneaking up on him. That's good.<span class="gensmall"></span>


